In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims March 2013 as Irish-American Heritage Month. He highlights the contributions of Irish immigrants to the United States, who came to pursue their dreams and find a better life. Despite facing hardships and prejudice, these immigrants never gave up on the idea that anyone, regardless of their background, can contribute to the American story. The President encourages Americans to celebrate Irish-American heritage and to retell stories of hard work and determination. He also emphasizes the strong bond between America and Ireland and their shared values. The proclamation calls for appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs to observe this month.